In the first article "Tried A Korean Skin Care Routine For A Month And This Is What Happened", this article addressed to the young women, how they can take care of their skin, the editor talks about trying Korean beauty products. By going to an esthetician, she wrote what happened week after week after using the products daily for a month. Its language is informal they use a lot of words used by young people like y'all,Â wacky, what the heck.
The second article "k beauty: The rise of Korean make-up in the West" is more formal than the first its audience is general public, it gives us information about Koreans and how they take care of their skin first by using k beauty products and how they become socially successful, and inspiration to the western cosmetics companies, the writer thinks that this phenomenon is rising and will not disappear anytime soon.